18:04.435 --> 18:06.494
# And then I say bo, add a "B" #

18:06.570 --> 18:10.666
# Then I say the name
and banana fanna and a fo #

18:10.741 --> 18:13.539
# And then I say the name again
with an "F," very plain #

18:13.610 --> 18:15.840
# And a fee fi and a mo #

18:15.913 --> 18:19.508
# And then I say the name again
with an "M" this time #

18:19.583 --> 18:22.381
# And there isn't any name
that I can't rhyme #

18:24.688 --> 18:26.781
# Pepper
Pepper, Pepper, bo bepper #

18:26.857 --> 18:28.347
# Banana fanna fo fepper #

18:28.425 --> 18:30.893
# Fee fi mo mepper #

18:30.961 --> 18:32.360
# Pepper #

18:33.964 --> 18:36.831
# But if the first two letters
are ever the same #

18:36.900 --> 18:39.698
# I drop them both
and say the name #

18:39.770 --> 18:42.796
# Like Bob, Bob
Drop the B's... bo ob #

18:42.873 --> 18:45.364
# For Fred, Fred
Drop the F's... fo red #

18:45.442 --> 18:48.309
# For Mary, Mary
Drop the M's... mo ary #

18:48.378 --> 18:51.370
# That's the only rule that is contrary #

18:52.816 --> 18:54.306
# Okay? #

18:54.384 --> 18:55.715
- # Now say bo #
- # Bo #

18:55.786 --> 18:57.549
- # Now Tony with a "B" #
- # Bony #

18:57.621 --> 19:00.249
- # Then banana fanna fo #
- # Banana fanna fo #

19:00.324 --> 19:03.259
- # Then you say the name again with an "F," very plain #
- # Fony #

19:03.327 --> 19:06.023
- # Then a fee fi and a mo #
- # Fee fi mo #

19:06.096 --> 19:09.065
- # Then say the name again with an "M" this time #
- # Mony #

19:09.133 --> 19:11.328
# And there isn't any name
that you can't rhyme #

19:11.401 --> 19:12.527
Whoo!

19:12.603 --> 19:14.833
# Kit, Kit, bo bit,
banana fanna fo fit #

19:14.905 --> 19:18.341
# Fee fi mo mit, Kit #

19:19.243 --> 19:25.614
# The name game ##

19:26.817 --> 19:29.752
[Whooping, Cheering]

19:29.820 --> 19:32.721
<i>##[Ends]</i>

19:32.789 --> 19:35.280
[Patients Chattering]

19:35.359 --> 19:37.020
Do you know your name?

19:41.131 --> 19:43.031
Your name is Judy Martin.

19:47.804 --> 19:49.294
Dr. Arden.

19:52.276 --> 19:55.211
Dr. Arden, what are you doing?
[Exhales]

19:55.279 --> 19:56.712
An afternoon feeding, Hans?

19:56.780 --> 19:58.441
That's unusual, isn't it?

19:58.515 --> 20:00.346
I asked you not to call me that.

20:00.417 --> 20:03.648
Oh, Hans, it's just us here after all.

20:03.720 --> 20:05.620
There is no "us."

20:05.689 --> 20:08.089
[Chuckles]
Don't tell me you're jealous.

20:10.661 --> 20:12.822
He didn't mean anything to me.

20:12.896 --> 20:14.761
<i>That</i> I believe.

20:16.633 --> 20:18.260
You know what I was thinking?

20:18.335 --> 20:22.499
Wouldn't it be fun and, uh,
therapeutically beneficial...

20:22.573 --> 20:24.473
if we gave her a transorbital lobotomy?

20:24.541 --> 20:26.941
Crack that thick skull open like a walnut?

20:27.010 --> 20:29.444
No.

20:29.513 --> 20:30.445
Why not?

20:30.514 --> 20:32.641
Because you wish it.

20:38.222 --> 20:40.417
[Man Grunting]

20:43.860 --> 20:45.487
[Gasps]

20:45.562 --> 20:47.689
The experiment is over.

20:53.403 --> 20:54.529
[Groans]

20:59.610 --> 21:01.100
[Chuckling]

21:01.178 --> 21:03.043
My, my.

21:03.747 --> 21:05.442
Quite a tantrum, Arthur.

21:06.416 --> 21:07.815
[Sighs]

21:07.884 --> 21:09.943
It's a farce.

21:12.022 --> 21:14.217
<i>Finita la commedia.</i>

21:18.395 --> 21:20.989
[Sobbing]

21:28.171 --> 21:31.106
You... have no idea what it means...

21:31.174 --> 21:33.142
to have lost you.

21:39.549 --> 21:41.540
Jesus Christ.

21:41.618 --> 21:43.813
You're being pitiful, Arthur.

21:46.356 --> 21:48.517
Then... have pity on me.

21:52.963 --> 21:55.295
[Groans, Moans]

22:05.075 --> 22:07.270
[Patients Chattering]

22:12.949 --> 22:16.407
Everyone, I'd like you all to stop what
you're doing and go to the common room.

22:16.486 --> 22:19.011
[Carl] Hang up your aprons
and line up over here.

22:19.089 --> 22:21.387
We'll all go together.

22:21.458 --> 22:23.585
- [Man] Come on, George.
- [Chattering Continues]

22:26.963 --> 22:30.956
Jude, will you remain here, please?

22:33.403 --> 22:36.770
The medication they give you
is strong, I know.

22:39.776 --> 22:42.768
It affects your motor skills. Here.

22:44.047 --> 22:47.642
Take your loaf and push it
with the heel of your hand.

22:49.353 --> 22:51.150
Like this.

22:58.395 --> 23:00.454
Oh. I'm all right.

23:01.498 --> 23:03.932
At least my hands are all right.

23:05.001 --> 23:06.764
I came to talk to you.

23:06.837 --> 23:09.965
It seems I don't know who else...

23:10.040 --> 23:13.009
I can unburden myself to.

23:13.076 --> 23:17.240
You've always been
a loyal and honest friend.

23:17.314 --> 23:20.943
You've always had
the gift of moral clarity.

23:21.017 --> 23:25.147
I owe you an apology, Jude.

23:25.222 --> 23:28.988
More than an apology.
There are no words for my regret.

23:34.765 --> 23:36.494
The devil...

23:36.566 --> 23:38.659
lives inside Sister Mary Eunice.

23:38.735 --> 23:40.635
You were right.

23:40.704 --> 23:43.366
I tried to cast it out, but I failed.

23:43.440 --> 23:46.603
In truth, it was an epic failure.

23:46.676 --> 23:49.440
She'll destroy everything.

23:50.781 --> 23:53.113
Why didn't I listen to you?

23:53.183 --> 23:55.208
Why was I so stubborn?

23:55.285 --> 23:57.981
She's destroyed you...

23:58.054 --> 24:00.420
and now she's destroyed me.

24:03.894 --> 24:05.953
My virtue is gone, Jude.

24:06.029 --> 24:10.363
She took it from me, violated me.

24:10.434 --> 24:12.732
I tried to resist, but...

24:14.538 --> 24:16.631
I don't know where else to turn.

24:16.706 --> 24:21.143
I'm struggling with whether
I should renounce my vows.

24:23.413 --> 24:24.903
[Sighs]

24:24.981 --> 24:27.609
I need your counsel.

24:27.684 --> 24:29.914
Should I confess and walk away...

24:29.986 --> 24:31.749
from my beloved church...

24:31.822 --> 24:35.314
and our dream?

24:41.431 --> 24:42.955
[Sniffles]

24:43.033 --> 24:44.762
What should I do?

24:46.169 --> 24:48.160
Kill her.

24:53.310 --> 24:56.006
And have Kit Walker
brought to my office at 3:00 today.

24:56.079 --> 24:57.603
Yes, Doctor.

24:57.681 --> 25:00.548
And I think for this session
we'll want to secure him in a straitjacket.

25:00.617 --> 25:01.641
Will do.

25:01.718 --> 25:04.152
That's Dr. Arden's office
around the corner.

25:04.221 --> 25:05.711
Thank you, Carl.

25:05.789 --> 25:07.620
I can take it from here.

25:12.028 --> 25:13.552
Dr. Arden?

25:13.630 --> 25:15.962
It's Oliver Thredson. Are you in?

25:19.669 --> 25:21.000
Dr. Arden?

25:25.609 --> 25:27.099
Are you here?

25:29.613 --> 25:32.605
Now, where would you keep
your sodium pentothal?

25:41.057 --> 25:43.855
[Woman Screaming]

25:51.668 --> 25:53.397
Dr. Arden?

25:56.840 --> 25:58.603
[Screaming Continues]

26:03.113 --> 26:05.104
[Screaming Continues]

26:06.950 --> 26:08.417
She's crowning.

26:11.254 --> 26:13.484
"Be strong in the Lord...

26:13.557 --> 26:15.821
and in the power of his might.

26:15.892 --> 26:17.826
Put on the whole armor of God...

26:17.894 --> 26:20.727
that ye may be able to stand
against the wiles of the devil"...

26:20.797 --> 26:24.528
[Together] "For we wrestle not
against flesh and blood"...

26:25.669 --> 26:27.796
"but against principalities...

26:27.871 --> 26:30.032
against powers...

26:30.106 --> 26:33.439
against rulers of the darkness
of this world...

26:33.510 --> 26:37.606
against spiritual wickedness
in high places."

26:40.116 --> 26:41.777
Are we having regrets, Father?

26:41.851 --> 26:45.116
Did our little tryst
turn your stomach into knots?

26:46.623 --> 26:48.989
Or are we ready for round two?

26:49.059 --> 26:52.392
I have to admit, I found your innocence...

26:52.462 --> 26:53.986
quite intoxicating.

26:54.064 --> 26:56.294
Don't touch me.

26:56.366 --> 26:59.392
We will never repeat
our indiscretion again.

26:59.469 --> 27:01.664
Well, now it's not what you want.

27:01.738 --> 27:04.298
You don't want to lay me on the ground.

27:04.374 --> 27:06.467
You want to bury me beneath it.

27:06.543 --> 27:09.376
That's why you're praying for strength.

27:09.446 --> 27:11.141
How will you kill me?

27:12.816 --> 27:15.080
A letter opener? No, I don't think so.

27:15.151 --> 27:18.746
Unless you hit pay dirt
on the first strike, it'll be messy.

27:18.822 --> 27:20.517
What else?

27:20.590 --> 27:24.048
You could bludgeon me
with the statue of St. Francis.

27:24.127 --> 27:25.822
That would be ironic...
[Chuckles]

27:25.895 --> 27:28.693
Considering that he renounced
his debauchery before becoming a saint...

27:28.765 --> 27:32.064
and you, Father,
living your life in complete reversal.

27:33.470 --> 27:36.735
Could you wrap your fingers
around my throat...

27:36.806 --> 27:38.364
[Whispering]
And squeeze?

27:38.441 --> 27:39.874
Hmm?

27:43.046 --> 27:45.446
Or will you use your rosary
like you did with Shelley?

27:45.515 --> 27:48.780
- I don't know what you're talking about.
- Oh.

27:48.852 --> 27:50.945
You have no secrets from me.

27:52.355 --> 27:55.085
Especially not after what we shared.
I know it all.

27:55.158 --> 27:57.183
But don't worry, Father.

27:57.260 --> 27:59.353
Your little fantasy about killing me...

28:00.630 --> 28:02.655
it hasn't put me off.

28:02.732 --> 28:04.529
Quite the opposite.

28:04.601 --> 28:07.900
I'm gonna make
all of your dreams come true.

28:07.971 --> 28:12.931
We will rise in the hierarchy
of the church together.

28:14.077 --> 28:15.567
Bishop...

28:16.179 --> 28:18.010
cardinal...

28:18.081 --> 28:20.049
dare we even say...

28:21.818 --> 28:23.308
[Whispering]
Pope?

28:24.954 --> 28:27.081
I know it's what you want.
Isn't it, Monsignor?

28:27.157 --> 28:29.489
The desires of the flesh,
they're nothing...

28:29.559 --> 28:35.395
compared to the rewards
of power and ambition.

28:37.767 --> 28:39.758
You don't know me.

28:39.836 --> 28:41.895
I know you're weak.

28:43.206 --> 28:46.607
But I'm strong enough for both of us.

28:46.676 --> 28:48.837
You're mine now...

28:48.912 --> 28:50.743
body and soul.

28:58.321 --> 29:01.051
I'm not yours. I never will be.

29:01.124 --> 29:03.854
I'd rather die than allow you
to defile the Church.

29:03.927 --> 29:06.794
Are you talking?
You've suddenly grown quite tiresome.

29:06.863 --> 29:07.887
You'll not win.

29:07.964 --> 29:09.955
You couldn't even defeat
Sister Mary Eunice.

29:10.033 --> 29:13.002
Her purity remains alive inside.
I know it.

29:13.069 --> 29:16.527
Don't make me reconsider
my largess, Timothy.

29:16.606 --> 29:20.133
I will cast you out and return Mary Eunice
to her state of grace.

29:22.912 --> 29:24.880
- [Groans]
- I gave you a chance, Timothy...

29:24.948 --> 29:26.973
but you've just pissed it away!

29:28.184 --> 29:30.846
I'm done with you...
and with your sweet nun.

29:30.920 --> 29:34.788
I'm about to devour
the last morsel of her soul.

29:37.594 --> 29:39.323
[Sobbing]

29:39.395 --> 29:41.158
[Gasping, Moaning]

29:44.467 --> 29:45.991
I'm sorry, Monsignor.

29:47.470 --> 29:49.631
I'm tired of fighting.

29:52.475 --> 29:54.705
I want to let go.

29:54.778 --> 29:58.714
Then let go of me, Sister.

30:41.124 --> 30:42.887
Take me.

30:44.194 --> 30:46.856
I'll take both of you.

31:00.677 --> 31:02.975
[Monsignor Howard]
We beseech thee, O Lord, in thy mercy...

31:03.046 --> 31:05.480
to have pity on the soul of thy handmaid.

31:05.548 --> 31:08.711
Restore to her that portion
of everlasting salvation...

31:08.785 --> 31:11.310
through Jesus Christ, our Lord.

31:13.723 --> 31:16.123
She's been released from Satan's grip.

31:16.192 --> 31:18.490
Satan's or yours?

31:18.561 --> 31:21.792
I was told she fell from the third floor.

31:21.865 --> 31:24.060
Evidently it was your grip
that failed her.

31:24.133 --> 31:26.601
Her everlasting soul has been set free.

31:27.570 --> 31:30.004
Now we must help it find rest.

31:31.207 --> 31:33.402
It's time to prepare her for burial.

31:33.476 --> 31:35.000
No.

31:35.078 --> 31:37.308
She needs to be cremated.

31:37.380 --> 31:40.144
Cremation is a pagan practice...

31:40.216 --> 31:42.741
and a denial of the doctrine
of resurrection.

31:42.819 --> 31:46.687
Monsignor, the very cells of her body
were corrupted by the devil.

31:47.657 --> 31:49.181
No.

31:49.259 --> 31:51.750
She has to be cremated.

31:51.828 --> 31:53.853
The crematorium here at Briarcliff?

31:53.930 --> 31:55.625
It's still fully functional.

31:55.698 --> 31:58.599
[Sighs]
Very well. I will assist.

31:59.335 --> 32:00.996
That won't be necessary.

32:04.107 --> 32:06.098
I want to do it myself.

32:10.713 --> 32:13.443
As a sign of sanctity...

32:13.516 --> 32:15.746
sometimes God permits the dead body...

32:15.818 --> 32:18.946
to emit an odor of sweet perfume.

32:20.223 --> 32:24.319
It was said that when
Santa Teresa de Ãvila died...

32:24.394 --> 32:28.660
the smell of roses lingered
in the convent for days.

32:28.731 --> 32:31.199
What do you smell now, Monsignor?

32:33.369 --> 32:35.394
Nothing but decay.

32:58.628 --> 33:00.152
3:00, right on time.

33:00.229 --> 33:02.857
Want me to stick around?
He's got some attitude today.

33:02.932 --> 33:05.264
We'll be just fine, Carl. Thank you.

33:07.070 --> 33:10.062
There's nothing you can do to me
to make me tell you where that tape's at.

33:10.139 --> 33:12.767
Oh, I'm well aware of that.
I diagnosed you long ago, Kit.

33:12.842 --> 33:16.107
I know you'd rather die
than give me what I want.

33:17.847 --> 33:21.112
But there's an impulse in you that runs
even deeper than your martyr complex...

33:21.184 --> 33:23.209
and that's your savior complex...

33:23.286 --> 33:25.550
particularly when it comes to women...

33:25.621 --> 33:27.350
and, one would assume...

33:29.759 --> 33:31.249
children.

33:35.164 --> 33:37.792
- Kit.
- Grace.

33:39.369 --> 33:42.532
No. That's close enough.

33:42.605 --> 33:44.402
[Baby Cooing]

33:44.474 --> 33:45.964
That's not possible.

33:47.210 --> 33:48.700
- You were...
- Dead?

33:48.778 --> 33:51.542
At least according
to Dr. Arden's postmortem report.

33:51.614 --> 33:54.139
Now, given Grace's condition...

33:54.217 --> 33:55.741
one would either have to, "A"...

33:55.818 --> 33:58.810
judge Arden as guilty of one of the most
egregious misdiagnoses...

33:58.888 --> 34:00.583
in the history of modern medicine...

34:00.656 --> 34:03.955
or conclude that
he's been up to something...

34:04.027 --> 34:07.258
quite extraordinary
in that laboratory of his.

34:07.330 --> 34:08.319
Grace...

34:08.998 --> 34:10.761
says that's your son.

34:14.036 --> 34:16.402
Now, what are we to make of that?

34:19.175 --> 34:20.835
Is it true?

34:22.478 --> 34:23.967
It's true.

34:26.382 --> 34:28.543
You believe her, don't you, Kit?

34:29.752 --> 34:31.811
What are you gonna do?

34:31.888 --> 34:34.652
That's entirely up to you.

34:52.308 --> 34:54.435
What the... What?

34:55.678 --> 34:59.045
I don't want to ruin it for you,
but... Spot jumps.

35:00.116 --> 35:01.947
Where is the tape, you bitch?

35:02.018 --> 35:04.851
Oliver, is that any way to speak to
the mother of your unborn child?

35:04.921 --> 35:06.855
I'm the only one
who knows where it is now.

35:06.923 --> 35:09.118
Kit's not going to find out.

35:09.192 --> 35:11.922
And if you do anything to him,
anything at all...

35:11.994 --> 35:13.655
or anyone else for that matter...

35:13.729 --> 35:16.391
I'll find a way to get it to the police.

35:16.466 --> 35:18.058
You know I can do it, Oliver.

35:18.134 --> 35:20.967
I'm goddamn plucky. Remember?

35:31.581 --> 35:33.071
Margaret.

35:37.653 --> 35:38.745
Kevin.

35:38.821 --> 35:41.984
And, uh, Milton.

35:42.058 --> 35:43.889
[Muttering]

35:43.960 --> 35:45.689
Doris... Dor...

35:45.761 --> 35:47.729
Dori...

35:47.797 --> 35:49.697
No. Dolly. Dolly.

35:51.267 --> 35:52.757
Clyde.

35:52.835 --> 35:54.598
Uh...

35:58.641 --> 36:01.769
- Mother?
- Hello, Jude.

36:01.844 --> 36:03.004
[Sighs]

36:03.079 --> 36:05.877
Mother... Superior.

36:05.948 --> 36:09.076
Claudia. Mother Claudia.

36:10.653 --> 36:13.053
The monsignor said
you were speaking my name.

36:14.524 --> 36:16.458
Wanted to say good-bye.

36:16.526 --> 36:18.289
Good-bye?

36:18.361 --> 36:20.386
I'm going to Rome.

36:21.464 --> 36:23.159
The monsignor...

36:23.232 --> 36:24.961
Taking me to Rome.

36:25.868 --> 36:27.961
We're going to be pope.

36:29.205 --> 36:31.036
We're getting married.

36:33.109 --> 36:34.872
He likes my cooking.

36:37.046 --> 36:39.139
I'm a rare bird.

36:40.016 --> 36:43.645
Is it warm in Rome now?

36:43.719 --> 36:47.211
She tried to steal... him away.

36:47.290 --> 36:51.056
She rubbed her naked body on him.
[Growls]

36:51.127 --> 36:53.925
Ravish Me Red. Ravish Me Red.

36:53.996 --> 36:55.588
Jude.

36:55.665 --> 36:57.428
He killed her.

36:57.500 --> 36:59.263
He had to.

36:59.335 --> 37:02.361
We're getting married in the Vatican.

37:02.438 --> 37:04.235
The devil was jealous.

37:04.307 --> 37:06.275
Try and rest your mind.

37:07.043 --> 37:09.034
You're a little confused.

37:11.847 --> 37:13.405
[Sniffles]

37:16.219 --> 37:19.814
Do you see that woman over there
smoking a cigarette?

37:21.490 --> 37:23.151
[Sighs]

37:23.226 --> 37:24.591
Yes.

37:24.660 --> 37:26.924
Her name is Lana Winters.

37:26.996 --> 37:28.486
She doesn't belong here.

37:28.564 --> 37:30.623
I put her here.

37:32.401 --> 37:34.596
Help her...

37:34.670 --> 37:36.535
get out.

37:57.994 --> 38:00.360
- [Clicks]
- [Flames Ignite]

38:43.739 --> 38:45.366
[Sobs]

38:59.155 --> 39:01.953
[Gears Clanking]

39:16.439 --> 39:18.737
[Arden Screams]

